# Shell script changelog

When editing any `*.sh` script in this repo, add a new **top** history line immediately after the shebang (newest first).

Format:

```bash
# YYYY.MM.DD - v. MAJOR.MINOR[.PATCH] - brief what changed
```

Rules:

- Use today's date (`YYYY.MM.DD`).
- Bump the version from the current top entry (usually patch: `0.15.11` → `0.15.12`; or minor/major when appropriate).
- Keep the description to one short line — what changed and why, not a diff dump.
- Do not edit or reorder older history lines.
- `print_version_banner` reads the first matching line — the new entry must stay on top.

Example:

```bash
#!/bin/bash

# 2026.07.15 - v. 1.4 - GIT_REPO_DIRECTORY: ${profile_location_dir}/github/github-bin
# 2026.07.15 - v. 1.3 - ...
```

After script changes in this repo: commit and push to `master` unless the user says otherwise.
